    <h1>Our Personal Journey with KCNQ5</h1>
    <p>
      Our family's journey into the world of genetic disorders began out of
      necessity and love. A few years ago, my grandson, now nine years old, was
      facing significant challenges with speech and intellectual development.
      Seeking answers and support, we turned to genetic testing, which led to
      his diagnosis with a mutation in the KCNQ5 gene.
    </p>
    <p>
      This discovery was both enlightening and daunting. It explained many of
      the difficulties he faced, but it also opened up a new realm of
      uncertainties. Although he has not experienced seizures, his doctors have
      informed us that this could happen at any time, a common symptom for many
      with this mutation.
    </p>
    <p>
      Motivated by my grandson's needs and the potential to help others in
      similar situations, I was inspired to establish this foundation. Our
      mission is to drive research and uncover effective treatments or a cure
      for KCNQ5-related conditions. We are at the beginning of our quest to
      build a supportive community and robust research initiative. While we have
      not yet secured 501(c)(3) status, our immediate goal is to engage with
      those who are determined to make a difference.
    </p>
